main event: An unidentified flying object was sighted over Lexington, Missouri on November 4, 1967.
interesting points: The object was described as dark, oval-shaped, and approximately 30 to 40 feet in diameter.
The object was estimated to be moving at a speed of 400-500 mph.
The report includes several black and white photographs, though they are blurry and do not clearly show the object.
The documents are marked as 'UNCLASSIFIED' and come from the Foreign Technology Division of the US Air Force.
The report is part of a larger case file numbered 11434, dated March 12, 1967.
photographs: yes, 5 blurry black and white photographs
